SOP: Crusher Jamming, High Vibration, and Toggle Plate Failure

1. Notify the casting area operator and shift manager immediately.
2. Stop the feeder conveyor and isolate the crusher motor following LOTO procedures.
3. Visually inspect the crushing chamber for oversized rocks or tramp metal (un-crushable material).
4. If the toggle plate has sheared, obtain a replacement toggle plate from spares inventory.
5. Safely clear the jammed materials using high-pressure water jets and mechanical crane hooks.
6. Check manganese jaw liners for excessive wear, cracks, or loose wedging bolts.
7. Inspect the eccentric shaft bearings for overheating, lubricant degradation, or seal damage.
8. Replace the toggle plate and reset the closed-side setting (CSS) shims to baseline parameters (80mm).
9. Lubricate the eccentric bearings with EP-2 grease using the manual grease gun if the central pump is offline.
10. Remove LOTO tags, verify clear chamber, start crusher motor under no-load condition, and confirm vibration levels are normal.
